The paper focuses on energy harvesting (EH) two-hop communications, which involves information theory (IT) and networked systems (NI). The use of multi-agent reinforcement learning (MA) suggests that the paper may also belong to the multi-agent systems (SY) sub-category. The problem of finding transmission policies can also be related to game theory (GT).
